{
  "texts": [
    "Quantization is the process when instead of rounding a representation, they add a uniform noise, thus maintaining the ability to backpropagate through the model.",
    "As a metric, Weighted Binary Cross-ntropy (WBCE) loss is used.",
    "Furthermore, an adaptive module takes care of the distortions and removes unnecessary voxels according to a threshold.",
    "Standardized geometry-based compression algorithms such as Moving Picture Experts Group (MPEG) exist that are outperformed by this method by at least 60% in the perspective of the Bjöntegaard Delta Rate (BDR).",
    "While traditional codecs perform better in the evaluation of human visual systems, deep neural network-based approaches are better at reconstructing spatial, textual, and structural features."
  ]
}